						               													<description>Los 7 Locos is a game of hidden identities in which players secretly embody the masks of one of seven great Argentine and Uruguayan writers. Keeping his identity to himself, each player must simulate, deceive and deduce before the others to win the Silvio Ballan Award for best storyteller.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OBJECTIVE OF THE GAME&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player must try to discover the identity of the other players without revealing their own. To achieve this, he must perform actions in order to obtain resources. He must then use these resources to discover information about the other players in order to eliminate them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The storytellers take turns and carry out one or several actions depending on the resources and the decisions they decide to make.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Thus, each player shows off their best capacities for imagination, lies, deception and deduction -embodying the skills of the different writers, most of the time without being them- while trying to unmask the rest of the players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The last player left without being eliminated wins...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
